Very hot temperatures in Gauteng, Mpumalanga, Free State and the Northern Cape are expected to drop from tomorrow onwards. CAPE TOWN The South African Weather Service says residents in Gauteng can expect a rainy Christmas once the heatwave subsides this weekend. Very hot temperatures in Gauteng, Mpumalanga, Free State and the Northern Cape are expected to drop from tomorrow onwards.The Weather Service s Lulama Theme says they are monitoring the western parts of KwaZulu-Natal for possible thunder storms. In general there s nothing really significant on the weather front. &quot; However, there s cold front that is approaching from the west. It s only going to affect the south-western parts of the Western Cape province and then move south of the country. 